As of September 22, 2020, it operated 353 stores, including 101 KFC stores in New Zealand, 62 KFC stores in Australia, 37 Taco Bell stores in Hawaii, 2 Taco Bell stores in New Zealand, 2 Taco Bell stores in Australia, 24 Pizza Hut stores in New Zealand, 38 Pizza Hut stores in Hawaii, 69 KFC stores in California, and 18 Carl's Jr. stores in New Zealand stores. RUA.NZ.summary: Rua Bioscience Limited, a pharmaceutical company, focuses on the research, cultivation, extraction, and manufacturing parts of the medicinal cannabis supply chain in New Zealand. Rua Bioscience Limited has research and commercial partnerships with Crown Research Institutes and Universities Collaboration; Medical Research Institute of New Zealand; and Plant and Food New Zealand. The company was formerly known as Hikurangi Cannabis Company Limited and changed its name to Rua Bioscience Limited in October 2019. Rua Bioscience Limited was founded in 2016 and is based in Gisborne, New Zealand.

The company provides its tree seedlings under the ArborGen brand name to forest land owners and managers primarily in the United States, Brazil, and Australasia. The company was formerly known as Rubicon Limited and changed its name to ArborGen Holdings Limited in September 2019. ArborGen Holdings Limited is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

S05.F.summary: Scales Corporation Limited engages in the agribusiness activities in New Zealand. The company operates through Food Ingredients, Horticulture, and Logistics segments. The Food Ingredients segment processes and markets food ingredients, such as pet food ingredients and juice concentrates. This segment also manufactures and sells apple, kiwifruit, and pear juice concentrates. The Horticulture segment is involved in growing, packaging, marketing, and exporting apples under the Mr Apple, Fern Ridge Fresh, Dazzle, and Posy brands. The Logistics segment provides supply chain services for exporters, importers, and FMCG businesses. This segment also engages in the sea and air freight of produce. It also provides insurance services. The company was founded in 1897 and is headquartered in Christchurch, New Zealand.

SAN.NZ.summary: Sanford Limited engages in farming, harvesting, processing, storing, and marketing of seafood products. It operates through Wildcatch and Aquaculture segments. The company catches and processes inshore and deepwater fish species, as well as farms, harvests, and processes mussels and salmon. Its seafood products include antarctic toothfish, arrow squid, barracouta, blue mackerel, gemfish, ghost shark, greenshell mussels, hake, hapuku, hoki, jack mackerel, john dory, kahawai, king salmon, lemon sole, ling, monkfish, new zealand sole, orange roughy, patagonian toothfish, red cod, scampi, silver warehou, smooth oreo dory, snapper, southern blue whiting, trevally, and yellowbelly flounder. The company also provides auction, wharf, and research services; and retails and wholesales seafood. It operates in New Zealand and Australia; Europe; North America; Japan, China, Hong Kong, South Korea, and the rest of Asia; Africa; the Middle East; the Pacific; and Central and South America. Sanford Limited was founded in 1881 and is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand.

SCT.NZ.summary: Scott Technology Limited, an investment holding company, designs, manufactures, sells, and services automated and robotic production lines, and processes for various industries in New Zealand and internationally. The company operates through Australasia Manufacturing, Americas Manufacturing, Europe Manufacturing and China Manufacturing segments. The company manufactures and sells automated laboratory sampling equipment for the mining industry; high temperature superconductor equipment; patented centrifuge technology for the honey and fish processing industries; automated guided vehicles under the Transbotics brand; band-saw machines under the BladeStop brand; and x-ray and sorting technology, as well as offers robot systems under the RobotWorx brand. It also offers industrial services and systems, which includes conventional and robot palletisers, depalletisers, pallet conveyors, case conveyors, and order preparation systems with stacker cranes and other material handling equipment, as well as software package Maestro+ under the Alvey brand name; and automated heavy gauge precision metal stamping equipment under the DC Ross brand. In addition, the company provides cryogen-free electromagnetic products, such as solenoids, current leads, coils, magnets, current systems, and magnetic resonance systems under the HTS-110 brand name; and sample preparation equipment under the ROCKLABS brand. It serves appliances, materials handling and logistics, meat processing, mining, and other industrial automation industries. Scott Technology Limited was founded in 1913 and is based in Dunedin, New Zealand.

SDL.NZ.summary: Solution Dynamics Limited provides customer communication solutions in New Zealand, Australia, Europe, and the United States. The company offers advanced digital asset management solutions, which combine a central repository to store, manage, and access brand assets, as well as associated accurate brand and product information together with integrated publishing applications; and communications content generation solutions, such as communication content generation workflows, digital asset and smart document ingestion, smart template ingestion, advanced database driven templates, online preview, multi-language capabilities, approval workflows, and advanced user rights management. It also provides automated workflows for communications personalization; content personalization and automated workflows for printed mail, email, and SMS; smart document and data driven templates; online preview and approval workflows; automated workflows for dispatch of personalized communications; automated workflows to effect print and mail house services; and access to print and mail house, database cleansing workflow, and bulk mail rates. In addition, the company offers communication logistics solutions comprising outbound and inbound communications management, high volume document scanning and data capture, conversion of file from paper to digital and bulk ingestion, meta-data tagging automation, managing sensitive and time critical documents, and outsourced digital archiving and document management; and post on demand solutions, such as access to self-service delivery portal, and drag and drop workflows, as well as automated postal mail, email and SMS workflows. Further, it provides print management, mail house and fulfilment, communications database cleansing, direct and transactional marketing, and business process and IT consultancy services, as well as API driven customer communication software. Solution Dynamics Limited was founded in 1996 and is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

SEK.NZ.summary: Seeka Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides orchard lease and management, and post harvest services to the horticulture industry primarily in New Zealand. It operates through Orchard Operations, Post Harvest Operations, and Retail Service Operations segments. The Orchard Operations segment offers on-orchard management services to orchard owners who produce kiwifruit, avocado, and kiwiberry crops. The Post Harvest Operations segment provides post-harvest services to the kiwifruit, avocado, and kiwiberry industries that include crops from the company's orchard management and lease operations, as well as crops from independent orchard owners. The Retail Service Operations segment offers fruit marketing services; and retail and ripening services for imported fruit produce, and operates a wholesale market. It also produces and sells apricots, avocado, cherries, European pears, kiwiberry, kiwifruit, nashi pears, plums, bananas, pineapple, and organics, as well as kiwi crush, kiwi crushies, and avocado oil to the retail sector and hospitals. The company was formerly known as Seeka Kiwifruit Industries Limited and changed its name to Seeka Limited in October 2016. Seeka Limited was founded in 1987 and is headquartered in Te Puke, New Zealand.

SKC.AX.summary: SkyCity Entertainment Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates in the gaming, entertainment, hotel, convention, hospitality, and tourism sectors in New Zealand and Australia. It operates through Skycity Auckland, Other New Zealand Operations, SkyCity Adelaide, and International Business segments. The company engages in the hotels and convention, food and beverage, car parking, sky tower, property investment, and other related activities. It also operates casinos in Auckland, Hamilton, Queenstown, and Wharf, New Zealand; and Adelaide, Australia, as well as various restaurants, bars, and conference facilities. As of June 30, 2020, the company operated 273 table games, 3,204 electronic gaming machines, 307 automated table games, 19 restaurants, 14 bars, and 635 hotel rooms. The company was incorporated in 1994 and is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand.

SKL.NZ.summary: Skellerup Holdings Limited manufactures, markets, and distributes technical polymer and elastomer products for various specialist industrial and agricultural applications. It operates through Agri and Industrial segments. The company offers food grade dairy rubberware, including liners and tubing products, and rubber footwear for agricultural applications; milk filters; milk liners, tubing, and accessories; feeding teats; dairy vacuum pumps; and dairy hygiene and livestock health management products, as well as mastitis prevention and mastitis detection equipment. It also provides sealing and waterproofing products for roofing, plumbing, and civil/underground applications; pipe seals, diaphragms, washers, gaskets, customized rubber moldings, check valves, O rings, disks, and other components for use in automotive, industrial, mining pipe, valve, and medical industries; high precision rubber and plastic components for the automotive, flow control, appliance, and industrial markets; and fabric reinforced diaphragms, and rubber metal seat valves and injector components. In addition, the company offers EVA, PE, and various blended foams for marine, sports, leisure, orthotic, and construction applications; foam and soft material products; and live wall systems for installation in new and existing chutes. It operates primarily in New Zealand, Australia, North America, the United Kingdom, Ireland, rest of Europe, Asia, and internationally. Skellerup Holdings Limited was founded in 1910 and is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

SKO.AX.summary: Serko Limited, a Software-as-a-Service technology business, provides computer software solutions for online travel bookings and expense management in New Zealand, Australia, North America, and internationally. The company offers Zeno Travel, an online booking tool that corporate travelers use to book flights, trains, hotels, rental cars, and airport transfers in line with their corporate travel policies; and Zeno Expense, which automates the process of corporate card and out-of-pocket expense submission, reconciliation, and reimbursement. It also provides Serko mobile, a mobile app for iPhones and android devices that gives users access to information and travel booking functionality on their mobile devices. The company sells and delivers its products through a network of travel management companies. Serko Limited was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand.

The company offers amphibious, foldable and semi-rigid, and rigid inflatable boats. It serves government, commercial, and recreational customers. The company was formerly known as Sealegs Corporation Limited and changed its name to Future Mobility Solutions Limited in January 2017. Future Mobility Solutions Limited was incorporated in 1987 and is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

SM1.AX.summary: Synlait Milk Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells dairy products in China, rest of Asia, the Middle East, Africa, New Zealand, Australia, and internationally. It offers liquid milk; milk powder related products; nutritional products, such as infant and adult nutritional powders; ingredients comprising skim milk powders and anhydrous milk fat; and specialized nutritional ingredients, such as lactoferrin. Investment properties comprise of freehold land, leasehold land, buildings and improvements that are held either to earn rental income or for capital appreciation or both. It seeks to invest in New Zealand. Stride Stapled Group is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

SPK.AX.summary: Spark New Zealand Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides telecommunications and digital services in New Zealand. It offers telecommunications, information technology, media, and other digital products and services, including mobile services; voice services; broadband services; Internet TV; cloud, security, and service management services; procurement and partner services; and managed data and networks services. The company also offers IT infrastructure, business and outsourced telecommunications, subscription video-on-demand, big data analytics and marketing automation, data center, and international wholesale telecommunications services. In addition, it provides local, national, and international telephone and data services; group insurance products; and mobile phone repair services. Further, the company retails telecommunications products and services; and distributes equipment. The company was formerly known as Telecom Corporation of New Zealand Limited and changed its name to Spark New Zealand Limited in August 2014. Spark New Zealand Limited was founded in 1987 and is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

SPN.NZ.summary: South Port New Zealand Limited provides and manages port and warehousing services in New Zealand. It operates the Port of Bluff in the province of Southland. The company offers pilotage, towage, berthage, and full marine services to international and coastal vessels, including southern fishing fleet. It also provides full container, break bulk, and bulk cargo services for the import of alumina, petroleum products, fertilizers, acids, stock foods, and cement products; and the export of aluminum, timber, logs, dairy, meat by-products, fishes, and woodchips. In addition, the company offers container tracking services; dry warehousing services for a range of industries, including dairy, forestry, stock feed, and general cargo; cold stores for chilled and frozen products; and open storage facilities for logs, containers, woodchips, sawn timber, steel, and others. Further, it handles project cargo, such as transformer weighing, wind farm material, hydroelectric power station tail race equipment, mining equipment, and tanks for tallow storage, as well as a range of machinery, including pleasure and fishing vessels. The company was founded in 1988 and is based in Bluff, New Zealand.

The company also engages in selling Eftpos terminals; and provides hardware, software, and maintenance and repairs services. The company serves 25,000 merchants with approximately 35,000 EFTPOS terminals. It serves retail, trade, taxi and transport, charities and schools, hospitality, and tourism industries. The company was incorporated in 1986 and is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

STG.AX.summary: Straker Translations Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the provision of translation services in Asia Pacific, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and North America. The company operates AI-POWERED RAY, a suite of customizable AI and automation translation tools that creates a first draft translation and matching the customer's content with one or more of the approximately 10,000 crowd-sourced human freelance translators for refinement. It offers corporate and business translation services, such as e-commerce translation, financial translation, human resources translation, legal document translation, marketing content translation, medical document translation, technical document translation, Website translation, audio and video translation, and document translation services, as well as desktop publishing services. The company also provides language translation services; machine translation services; immigration, legal, and ECFMG translation services; birth, death, and marriage certificates translation services; and passports, visa, medical, personal and private docs, drivers license, police and legal documents, academic records and transcripts, insurance, and other document translation services, as well as translation automation solutions comprising API translation solutions. Its platform supports African, Asian, Eastern European, European, Indian, Middle Eastern, and other languages. Straker Translations Limited was incorporated in 1999 and is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand.

STU.NZ.summary: Steel & Tube Holdings Limited provides steel products, services, and solutions in New Zealand. The company offers structural steel, bar and plate products, and hollow steel sections; pipe and cable support products that include clip pipes, cables, and wire suspension systems; and stainless steel products, such as coils, sheets, plates, pipes, hygienic tube and associated fittings, and various structural bars, handrails, and architectural products to large scale projects and to the stainless steel fabricators, major corporations, and businesses in the construction, diary, water, food processing, energy, and manufacturing sectors. It also provides architectural stainless steel and other metals; chain and rigging services and solutions; pipes, valves, and fittings for petrochemical, power generation, mining, irrigation, fire protection, building services, and water and wastewater industries; profile metal roofing, cladding, and rainwater products; HST purlins and top hats; and fastening solutions for construction, manufacturing, general engineering, and fabrication sectors. In addition, the company offers fabricated reinforcing steel meshes, bars, ties, piles, beams, and columns for use in building and construction industry; engineered reinforcing solutions; composite floor decks; industrial consumable products, such as grinding discs and cut off wheels, adhesives and sealants, drills and drill sets, CRC and ROCOL, and industrial tools; galvanised, hot- and cold-rolled, aluminised, enameled, and colorsteel sheet and coil solutions; and reinforcing, fencing, fence panels, wire, gates, and nail products for use in agricultural, horticultural, and viticultural industries, as well as rural construction sector. Steel & Tube Holdings Limited was founded in 1953 and is based in Auckland, New Zealand.

TAH.NZ.summary: Third Age Health Services Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides managed health care services for aged residential care facilities, private hospitals, and secure dementia facilities. The company was formerly known as Medplace Limited and changed its name to Third Age Health Services Limited in April 2011. Third Age Health Services Limited was incorporated in 2010 and is based in Napier, New Zealand.

TGG.NZ.summary: T&G Global Limited, together with its subsidiaries, grows, markets, distributes, and exports fresh produce under the JAZZ, envy, enza, pacific rose, LOTATOES, sunfirst, BEEKIST, and ORCHARD RD brands. It operates through Apples, International Produce, New Zealand Produce, Processed Foods, and Other segments. The company offers apples, pears, grapes, kiwifruit, asparagus, and tomatoes; citrus products, including lemons, mandarins, navel oranges, limes, grapefruit, and tangelos; cherries; blueberries, strawberries, and kiwi berries; and other stone fruits, as well as potatoes and other produce. It also cool stores and packs apples; sells, trades in, and markets processed foods; and engages in the horticulture, fruit and produce wholesale distribution, and fruit variety development and propagation activities. In addition, the company is involved in the processed foods broking, captive insurance provision, leased property holding, and water supply businesses, as well as the provision of in-market and fruit import and shared services. It sells its fresh produce in approximately 60 countries. The company was formerly known as Turners & Growers Limited and changed its name to T&G Global Limited in May 2015. The company was founded in 1883 and is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand. T&G Global Limited is a subsidiary of BayWa Aktiengesellschaft.

THL.NZ.summary: Tourism Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a tourism company in Australia, New Zealand, and the United States. The company operates through New Zealand Rentals, New Zealand Tourism Group, Australia Rentals, and United States Rentals segments. It engages in the design, manufacture, rental, and sale of motor homes, campervans, caravans, 4WD vehicles, and RV accessories; and other tourism related activities. The company offers its vehicles under the Maui, Britz, and Mighty rental brands, as well as owns and operates the Road Bear RV, Just Go, El Monte RV, and Mighway rentals and sales brands. It also operates hop on and hop off guided buses under the Kiwi Experience name; operates Waitomo Glowworm caves, Ruakuri caves, and Aranui caves; provides water rafting in the subterranean rivers that flow through the Ruakuri cave system; and operates Waitomo Homestead, a refurbished restaurant. The company was formerly known as The Helicopter Line and changed its name to Tourism Holdings Limited in 1996. Tourism Holdings Limited was incorporated in 1984 and is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand.

TLL.NZ.summary: TIL Logistics Group Limited operates as a freight and logistics company in New Zealand. It operates through International, Specialist, Freighting, Warehousing & Logistics, and Bulk Liquids segments. The company offers international freight forwarding services for the oil and gas industry; shipping agency services; transport and lifting solutions for oversized and large items, as well as advisory services; freight transport; warehousing and supply chain solutions; and delivery of various bulk liquid goods. It also provides heavy haulage, container transport, shipping, storage and distribution, and household removals and storage services. In addition, the company offers custom clearance work, port services, ship husbandry, crew matters, tank cleaning, and various services for importers/exporters, as well as asset leasing services. It owns and operates a fleet of approximately 2,300 trucks, trailers, forklifts, and light vehicles, as well as petroleum product dangerous goods road tanker fleets under the Pacific Fuel Haul brand name. The company is headquartered in New Plymouth, New Zealand.

TPW.NZ.summary: Trustpower Limited engages in the development, ownership, and operation of electricity generation facilities in New Zealand. It operates through Generation and Retail segments. The company is also involved in the retail sale of electricity and gas; and provision of telecommunications services, which include wireless broadband and mobile services to homes and businesses. As of November 5, 2020, it operated approximately 263,000 electricity customer connections, 42,000 gas customer connections, and 106,500 telecommunications customer connections, as well as owned 25 hydropower schemes with a total installed capacity of 495 megawatts. The company was founded in 1915 and is based in Tauranga, New Zealand. Trustpower Limited is a subsidiary of Infratil Limited.

TRA.AX.summary: Turners Automotive Group Limited engages in the automotive retail business in New Zealand and Australia. It operates through five segments: Automotive Retail, Finance, Credit Management, Insurance, and Corporate & Other. The company buys and sells second hand cars, trucks, machinery, and commercial goods under the Turners and Buy Right Cars brand names. It also provides financial solutions for personal, vehicle, and small to medium business customers under the Oxford Finance brand; and underwrites and distributes a range of life and non-life consumer insurance products under the Autosure and Greenwich Life Insurance brands. The company distributes electricity to residential and commercial customers in Auckland, from Wellsford to Papakura through its network consisting of approximately 18,000 kilometers of overhead lines and underground cables; natural gas to customers; bulk LPG to commercial customers; and bottled LPG to commercial and residential customers. In addition, it offers Powster, a studio that provides creative services to the film and music industry, as well as creates products to help users engage with entertainment content; Flicks, an authoritative guide for cinemas; Numero, box office tracking and reporting software for film distributors and cinemas; and Cinema Intelligence and movieXchange solutions. VHP.NZ.summary: Vital Healthcare Property Trust is a real estate investment trust externally managed by Vital Healthcare Management Limited. The firm investments in health and medical related properties in New Zealand and Australia. It undertakes acquisition or development of medical or healthcare-related properties such as surgical and medical facilities, geriatric and continuing care facilities primary healthcare facilities, and health support facilities. The fund may invest in conjunction with other health service providers. It was formerly known as ING Medical Properties Trust and Calan Healthcare Properties Trust.

VHT.AX.summary: Volpara Health Technologies Limited provides breast imaging analytics and analysis products for the early detection of breast cancer in the medical device and practice management software industry. The company offers VolparaEnterprise software, a cloud-based breast imaging analytics platform that delivers real-time quality assurance and performance monitoring solutions; and VolparaDensity software, which provides volumetric breast density measurements and a breast density category. It also offers VolparaDose, which compute the personalized x-ray dose to the patient based on breast density; VolparaPressure that computes the compression pressure applied to the breast during a mammogram; VolparaScorecard+, a clinical decision-support tool that provides insights for breast care; VolparaLive, a real-time decision support system, which analyzes patient positioning and compression, and offers real-time feedback; and VolparaRisk, a risk assessment software that delivers objective insight to radiologists for supplemental screening and testing. In addition, the company provides Aspen Breast, a workflow driven tracking and reporting solution; and Aspen Lung, a lung screening workflow tool that facilitates lung CT screening reporting and data system. Volpara Health Technologies Limited operates in North America, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and the APAC countries. The company was formerly known as Matakina Technology Ltd. and changed its name to Volpara Health Technologies Limited in October 2015. Volpara Health Technologies Limited was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in Wellington, New Zealand.

VTL.NZ.summary: Vital Limited provides mobile radio networks and high speed broadband services in New Zealand. The company operates in two segments, Wireless Networks and Wired Networks. It offers fibre and Ethernet solutions; and broadband connectivity and ancillary related services to a range of wholesale customers and end users. The company also provides data and GPS tracking products, as well as finance leasing services. It serves government, civil defense, emergency service, health, utility, public transport, education, logistics and freight, agriculture, and channel partner customers. The company was formerly known as TeamTalk Limited and changed its name to Vital Limited in July 2019. The company was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Wellington, New Zealand.

WDT.NZ.summary: Wellington Drive Technologies Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures, markets, and sells energy saving and electronically commutated (EC) motors, controllers, and fans; and develops Internet of Things solutions and software worldwide. The company also provides proximity marketing solutions comprising iPX Platform that connects customer's digital marketing efforts to SCS beacons or other proximity devices; Mobile Coupon Factory, which operates as an online agency that facilitates in the design, development, and deployment of integrated mobile marketing solutions; ScreenSmarts, which integrates with digital media screens to silently detect the presence of customers and interrupt normal sign content programming to display personalized contextual offers or information. Its products are used in supermarket and supermarket refrigeration, beverage merchandising, and food service applications. The company was formerly known as Cadac Limited and changed its name to Wellington Drive Technologies Limited in September 1996. Wellington Drive Technologies Limited was founded in 1986 and is headquartered in Auckland, New Zealand.
